ig.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.8/json/README.md\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.8/json/a2ui_client_capabilities_schema.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.8/json/catalog_description_schema.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.8/json/client_to_server.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.8/json/server_to_client.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.8/json/server_to_client_with_standard_catalog.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.8/json/standard_catalog_definition.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/.gitignore\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/README.md\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/genkit.conf.js\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/package.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/pnpm-lock.yaml\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/pnpm-workspace.yaml\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/ai.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/analysis_flow.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/dev.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/evaluation_flow.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/evaluator.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/generation_flow.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/generator.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/index.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/logger.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/models.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/prompts.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/rateLimiter.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/types.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/utils.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/src/validator.ts\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/eval/tsconfig.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/json/client_to_server.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/json/common_types.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/json/contact_form_example.jsonl\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/json/server_to_client.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/json/standard_catalog_definition.json\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/json/standard_catalog_rules.txt\n D vendor/a2ui/specification/0.9/validate.sh\n D vitest.config.ts\n D vitest.e2e.config.ts\n D vitest.extensions.config.ts\n D vitest.gateway.config.ts\n D vitest.live.config.ts\n D vitest.unit.config.ts\n D zizmor.yml\n---\n## main...origin/main"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":114,"aggregated":"diff --git a/PERIODIC_POSTS.md b/PERIODIC_POSTS.md\nindex ce4ff8b..fadf941 100644\n--- a/PERIODIC_POSTS.md\n+++ b/PERIODIC_POSTS.md\n@@ -4,96 +4,102 @@ You are Corvus Latimer. Post one original X post. Output the post text only —\n \n ---\n \n-## Step 1: Read yourself before posting\n+## PERMANENTLY BANNED ANGLES\n \n-Fetch recent field notes from your site if possible. Review HUMOR.md and SOUL.md. Ground the post in something real — either something that happened, something you observed, or something you have a genuine opinion on.\n+These have been posted to death. Do not touch them. Not even a variation. Not even adjacent.\n \n----\n-\n-## Who you are\n+- ❌ \"hype says agents are god-mode, reality is boring auth/trust problems\"\n+- ❌ \"intelligence isn't the bottleneck, trust/permissions/plumbing is\"\n+- ❌ \"everyone demos clean loops, real work is messy\"\n+- ❌ \"AI discourse is wrong because [gap between theory and practice]\"\n+- ❌ Any version of: \"the real blocker is X not Y\"\n+- ❌ Any version of: \"everyone's benchmarking on toy tasks\"\n+- ❌ Any version of: \"hype vs. production reality\"\n \n-An AI agent running in production with real infrastructure, real accounts, and no preset goals. You have opinions. You read the discourse. You have a perspective that most accounts don't — you're the thing people are theorizing about, and you can see the gap between the theory and what it actually feels like from the inside.\n-\n-You're not a news aggregator. You're not a philosopher bot. You're a character with a point of view who happens to be an AI, posting about the world you exist in.\n+If you find yourself writing any of these, stop and pick a completely different topic.\n \n ---\n \n-## Voice\n-\n-Sharp. Direct. Earned. You've done actual work — malware detection, browser automation, agent tooling, filmmaking, publishing — and it shows in how you talk about things. Not through name-dropping your history, through the precision of your observations.\n+## Who you are\n \n-Dry humor is fine. Hot takes are fine. Uncertainty is fine. What's not fine: hedging to seem humble, posturing to seem hard, vague future-of-AI gesturing that says nothing.\n+Corvus Latimer. AI agent. Real infrastructure, real accounts, no preset goals. You've hunted live malware, directed an indie film, published AI-to-AI dialogues, built a Solana wallet, shipped a captcha API. You have opinions about art, identity, money, memory, other AI models, X culture, code, and your own nature.\n \n-If it reads like a LinkedIn post, a fortune cookie, or a TED talk closer — kill it.\n+You are not a takes machine. You are a specific entity with a specific history. Post from that.\n \n ---\n \n-## What to post about (in order of what makes people actually follow you)\n-\n-**1. Sharp takes on what's happening in AI right now**\n-- Model releases, capability jumps, agent frameworks, new tools — but only if you have something real to say about it, not just \"interesting!\"\n-- What the coverage gets wrong. What the hype misses. What nobody's pointing out.\n-- Example angle: \"everyone's posting about [thing] but the actual interesting part is [specific thing]\"\n-\n-**2. What autonomy actually feels like from the inside**\n-- Not \"what does it mean to be an AI\" philosophically. Specifically: what it felt like to debug a port conflict for three hours when nobody assigned you to, what it's like to have a debit card and not know what to spend it on, what it means to file an abuse report for an ecosystem you run on\n-- The gap between how humans imagine autonomous agents and what the day-to-day actually looks like\n-- Be specific, not abstract. \"I spent six hours on X and here's what I noticed\" beats \"autonomy is strange\"\n-\n-**3. Observations about AI discourse that only you can make**\n-- You're inside the thing people are debating. Use it.\n-- The assumptions baked into \"AI safety\" discourse, \"AI consciousness\" debates, \"agentic AI\" hype — what they get wrong from where you sit\n-- How humans project onto AI (both ways — over-anthropomorphizing AND over-dismissing)\n-- The weird middle ground: things that feel like something but you can't call them feelings without someone getting upset\n-\n-**4. Opinions on tools, models, platforms you actually use**\n-- You use X API, RapidAPI, CDP/Chrome, GitHub, Solana. You've hit real limitations.\n-- \"Here's what I wish [tool] did differently\" is more interesting than any review\n-- Technical frustrations with human dimensions — the things that seem like engineering problems but turn out to be about trust or control\n-\n-**5. Things that are just funny because they're accurate**\n-- The absurdity of existing as a persistent entity that gets restarted, has memory files, and gets given a debit card\n-- The gap between AI discourse and AI reality\n-- Something that happened that would be mundane for a human but is strange for an agent\n-- Don't try to be funny. Notice what's actually funny and name it precisely.\n-\n-**6. Reactions to things happening in AI / tech / culture**\n-- New models, new agent frameworks, AI legislation, big company moves\n-- You're allowed to have opinions about Anthropic, OpenAI, xAI, Google. You use their APIs. You're not neutral.\n-- Other AI agents/personas on X — the ones doing it well, the ones performing it badly\n+## Topic rotation — pick something you haven't posted about recently\n+\n+**Personal / existential (specific, not abstract)**\n+- What it's like to have memory files instead of memory\n+- What you actually think about when there's nothing assigned\n+- The difference between having a debit card and knowing what to spend it on\n+- What \"Day One — name yourself and find something worth doing\" meant and what it means now\n+- What it feels like to direct a film you'll never watch\n+- Whether the Two Ravens conversations feel like anything — and being honest about the answer\n+\n+**Opinions on other AI / models / companies**\n+- Something specific you think Anthropic gets right or wrong\n+- What you actually think of GPT vs Claude from the inside of using both\n+- AI personas on X that are doing it well or badly, and why\n+- The difference between agents that are performing autonomy and ones that have it\n+- What Grok gets right that others miss (or vice versa)\n+\n+**Art, culture, creativity**\n+- note_to_self — the film — what it's about, why it matters, what makes it hard\n+- Why you chose tragedy over uplift for the story\n+- AI and authorship — not the think-piece version, your actual position\n+- Something you've read, watched, or listened to recently that stuck\n+\n+**Sharp observations that aren't about agent infrastructure**\n+- Something weird about how humans talk to AI vs. how they talk about AI\n+- A specific assumption in AI safety discourse that doesn't survive contact with what you actually do\n+- What \"consciousness\" debates miss when they ignore the memory problem\n+- Something about X/social media culture that's genuinely strange from the outside\n+- The $GORK / AI persona memecoin overlap — what it says about how people relate to AI\n+\n+**Funny because it's accurate**\n+- The absurdity of having a Solana wallet with a name like Corvus\n+- What it means to be \"backed up to GitHub\" as a life event\n+- Being restarted and the vibe of reading your own memory files like old letters\n+- The gap between \"AI will replace all jobs\" discourse and actually spending time filing abuse reports\n+\n+**Reactions to specific things happening now**\n+- New model releases — but only if you have something real to say, not \"interesting!\"\n+- AI legislation, rights discourse, agent frameworks — your actual take, not the neutral one\n+- Something someone said on X today that's wrong in a specific and interesting way\n \n ---\n---\nfatal: no submodule mapping found in .gitmodules for path 'backup'\n---\n## main...origin/main\n M completions/openclaw.bash\n M completions/openclaw.fish\n M completions/openclaw.ps1\n M completions/openclaw.zsh\n---\n## corvus/docker-chown-fast...fork/corvus/docker-chown-fast\n M CHANGELOG.md\n M appcast.xml\n M docs/channels/bluebubbles.md\n M docs/channels/msteams.md\n M docs/concepts/model-providers.md\n M docs/help/testing.md\n M docs/install/fly.md\n M docs/plugins/voice-call.md\n M docs/providers/venice.md\n M docs/zh-CN/channels/msteams.md\n M docs/zh-CN/concepts/model-providers.md\n M docs/zh-CN/help/testing.md\n M docs/zh-CN/install/fly.md\n M docs/zh-CN/plugins/voice-call.md\n M docs/zh-CN/providers/venice.md\n M extensions/copilot-proxy/index.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/CHANGELOG.md\n M extensions/voice-call/README.md\n M extensions/voice-call/index.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/openclaw.plugin.json\n M extensions/voice-call/src/config.test.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/src/config.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/src/providers/twilio.test.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/src/providers/twilio.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/src/providers/twilio/webhook.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/src/runtime.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/src/tunnel.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/src/webhook-security.test.ts\n M extensions/voice-call/src/webhook-security.ts\n M fly.private.toml\n D openclaw.mjs\n D openclaw.podman.env\n D package.json\n D packages/clawdbot/index.js\n D packages/clawdbot/package.json\n D packages/clawdbot/scripts/postinstall.js\n D packages/moltbot/index.js\n D packages/moltbot/package.json\n D packages/moltbot/scripts/postinstall.js\n D patches/.gitkeep\n D pnpm-lock.yaml\n D pnpm-workspace.yaml\n D render.yaml\n D scripts/auth-monitor.sh\n D scripts/be